---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About CoursePicked" description="We're learners who got tired of wasting money on overhyped courses. Here's who we are and why we started CoursePicked.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#1E3A5F] to-[#2d4a6f] text-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="bg-[#10B981]/20 text-[#10B981] text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-1 rounded-full">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-users mr-2"></i>about
        </span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 font-['Nunito'] text-white">About CoursePicked</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-blue-100 max-w-2xl">
        We're the friend who's already taken the course. Here's our story.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1E3A5F] mb-4 font-['Nunito']">Learn Smarter, Not Harder</h2>
        <p class="text-[#4B5563] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          We've all been there. You find a course that looks amazing—great marketing, lots of students, promises of transformation. You buy it. And then... disappointment. The content is outdated, the instructor is boring, or it just doesn't deliver what it promised.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#4B5563] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          We built CoursePicked because we were tired of wasting money (and time) on overhyped courses. We wanted <strong class="text-[#1E3A5F]">honest reviews from people who actually complete the courses</strong>—not just skim the first few videos.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1E3A5F] mb-4 mt-10 font-['Nunito']">How We Review Courses</h2>
        <p class="text-[#4B5563] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Every course we review gets the full treatment. We don't just watch a trailer and read some reviews. We actually enroll, complete the assignments, and track our progress from start to finish. That's the only way to know if a course delivers on its promises.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-[#F3F4F6] rounded-xl p-6 my-8 border border-gray-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-[#1E3A5F] mb-3 flex items-center gap-2 font-['Nunito']">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved text-[#10B981]"></i> Our Promise
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-[#4B5563]">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check text-[#10B981] mt-1"></i>
              <span>We actually complete the courses we review</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check text-[#10B981] mt-1"></i>
              <span>Platforms cannot pay for positive reviews</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check text-[#10B981] mt-1"></i>
              <span>We disclose affiliate relationships clearly</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check text-[#10B981] mt-1"></i>
              <span>If a course sucks, we'll tell you (even if we lose money)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-check text-[#10B981] mt-1"></i>
              <span>We update reviews when courses change</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1E3A5F] mb-4 mt-10 font-['Nunito']">Get in Touch</h2>
        <p class="text-[#4B5563] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          Have a question? Want us to review a specific course? Just want to chat about learning? We'd love to hear from you.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-[#4B5563]">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-envelope text-[#10B981] w-6"></i>
            <span>hello@coursepicked.com</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <i class="fa-brands fa-x-twitter text-[#10B981] w-6"></i>
            <span>@coursepicked</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <i class="fa-brands fa-youtube text-[#10B981] w-6"></i>
            <span>youtube.com/@coursepicked</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
